<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,259,1001,1025]" box="[144,259,1001,1025]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[144,259,1001,1025]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,259,1001,1025]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,774,1051,1585]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
This genus differs from other genera of the Australian ‘Ctenocerini’ 
<emphasis box="[284,339,1083,1105]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans HE" box="[349,486,1083,1105]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Australian Entomological Society" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="244 - 252" part="11" refId="ref11998" refString="Evans HE. 1972. The tribe Ctenoceratini in Australia (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society 11, 244 - 252." title="The tribe Ctenoceratini in Australia (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae)" type="journal article" year="1972">Evans (1972)</bibRefCitation>
by the unique combination of the following female features: clypeus much narrower than lower frons, truncate apically (
<figureCitation box="[456,530,1147,1169]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
); labrum fully exserted, sometimes bent backward at right angle to clypeus; lower frons laterally to antennal sockets deeply depressed; vertex moderately convex between eye tops, its upper margin chevron-shaped in frontal view; scape slightly produced apicomedially but not attaining apical margin of pedicel, with medial face flattened, smooth and polished and lateral face slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[151,256,1370,1393]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3b–d</figureCitation>
); gena, in dorsal view, thinner than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1855" box="[670,767,1371,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Maurillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[670,767,1371,1393]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Maurillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, gently receding posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[435,513,1403,1425]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
); pronotum with anterior face vertical, flattened and polished, forming right angle with dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[235,310,1467,1489]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
), anterior margin of pronotal dorsum convex in dorsal view, not tuberculate submedially, barely depressed medially (
<figureCitation box="[243,316,1531,1553]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
); and tarsal claws cleft (
<figureCitation box="[554,620,1531,1553]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
), the condition being unique tothe Australian ‘Ctenocerini’ 
<emphasis box="[576,631,1563,1585]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans HE" box="[636,770,1563,1585]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Australian Entomological Society" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="244 - 252" part="11" refId="ref11998" refString="Evans HE. 1972. The tribe Ctenoceratini in Australia (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society 11, 244 - 252." title="The tribe Ctenoceratini in Australia (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae)" type="journal article" year="1972">Evans (1972)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,285,1628,1652]" box="[144,285,1628,1652]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[144,285,1628,1652]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,285,1628,1652]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,217,1694,1716]" box="[144,217,1694,1716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[144,217,1694,1716]" fontSize="9" level="4" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[144,217,1694,1716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Female</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[144,774,1742,1956]" lastBlockId="8.[813,1443,142,1092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Head wider than high. Vertex with posterior margin shallowly and broadly emarginate in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[541,614,1774,1796]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
). Distance from eye tops to vertex crest, in lateral view, less than tenth of eye height (
<figureCitation box="[219,291,1838,1860]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). Frons notverybroad (MID/TFD 
<emphasis box="[639,659,1837,1860]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">&lt;</emphasis>
0.6); upper frons flattened and polished (
<figureCitation box="[444,518,1870,1892]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
); lower frons, in middle, sloping downward between antennal sockets. Ocellar triangle very flat (
<figureCitation box="[261,344,1934,1956]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
). Posterior ocelli at level of eye tops (
<figureCitation box="[821,892,142,164]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). Clypeus slightly depressed sublaterally, convex medially; lateral margin nearly vertical; apicolateral corner broadly rounded. Labrum with apical margin barely convex. Malar space very short. Mandible stout with small tooth removed from apical point on inner margin. Antenna short and slender. Gena not very thick, in profile gently narrowing above and below (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1387,302,324]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). Uppermost portion of occipital suture situated slightly below vertex crest (
<figureCitation box="[881,961,366,388]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
). Occiput not very large, compared with in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1855" box="[813,910,398,420]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Maurillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,910,398,420]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Maurillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[924,999,398,420]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[144,180,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[266,1320,130,1188]" captionTargetId="figure-272@2.[263,1323,127,1191]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Maurillus argenticapitis, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of antenna, ventrolateral view; (c) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (d) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (e) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; (f) fore wing and anterior part of hind wing; (g) head and mesosoma, dorsal view; (h) apical part of fore tibia, dorsal view; (i) right fore tarsus, dorsal view; and (j) right hind pretarsus, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (j), 0.5 mm for (h) and (i) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627875" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627875/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Figs 
<quantity box="[974,999,398,420]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="g" value="1.0">1g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1048,1074,398,420]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">3c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[813,1443,142,1092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Pronotal dorsum with anterior margin convex in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[821,893,462,484]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
); shoulder slightly swollen. Mesoscutum flattened, with posterolateral margin not reflexed. Discs of scutellum and metanotum flattened at same level as mesoscutum. Propodeum short and rugose on both dorsum and declivity (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1356,558,580]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1329,1356,558,580]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); declivity completely flattened for reception of anterior face of T1, longer than dorsum, separated from dorsum by blunt carina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[813,1443,142,1092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fore femur slightly thinner than mid femur. Dorsal apex of fore tibia with short stout decurved spines interiorly and exteriorly. Fore tarsomeres 2–4 combined much shorter than fore tarsomere 1. Mid and hind tibiae with short spines in three rows dorsally and ivory-white spurs. Tarsomere 5 of all legs beneath without spines.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[813,1443,142,1092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fore wing crossvein 
<emphasis box="[1048,1092,846,868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">cu-a</emphasis>
originating distal to point of separation of vein 
<emphasis box="[934,1029,878,900]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M + CuA</emphasis>
, very oblique to vein 
<emphasis box="[1248,1263,878,900]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1278,1351,878,900]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3h</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[813,1443,142,1092]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Metasoma not short, slightly broader than mesosoma (
<figureCitation box="[821,887,942,964]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<date box="[866,887,942,964]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">3i</date>
</figureCitation>
). T1 abruptly narrowing anteriorly; anterior face vertical and flat, fitting against propodeal declivity (
<figureCitation box="[1249,1317,974,996]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[145,181,1642,1664]" captionTargetBox="[305,1284,130,1609]" captionTargetId="figure-80@4.[302,1287,127,1611]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Maurilloides nigrisoma, sp. nov., holotype female.(a) Head, anterior view; (b) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsal view; (c) head and anterior part of mesosoma, dorsolateral view; (d) scape, dorsal view; (e) head and mesosoma, lateral view; (f) left hind pretarsus, lateral view; (g) metapostnotum and propodeum, posterodorsal view; (h) fore wing; (i) posterior part of mesosoma and metasoma, dorsal view; and (j) posterior part of propodeum and metasoma, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.1 mm for (f) and 1 mm for others." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4627881" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4627881/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 3j</figureCitation>
). Transverse groove on S2 distinctly impressed at about basal third. T6 with several long stiff bristles. S6 slightly compressed laterally without median carina.
</paragraph>
