<paragraph blockId="8.[813,1442,1454,1508]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The generic name is derived from a morphological similarity to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1855" box="[813,910,1486,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Maurillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,910,1486,1508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Maurillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name is considered masculine in gender.
</paragraph>
